The feasibility of the CuNPs-based simultaneous fluorescence sensor was verified by the spiked recovery method in Table 3
                        . Surprising, acceptable recovery rates (97.34%–102.57%) and relative standard deviations (RSD %) (2.56–5.76%) were acquired for spiked VB2 tablet and orange samples. Therefore, the F-CuNPs fluorescent probe has a good potential for detecting VB2 in actual samples. Similarly, satisfactory recovery rates (97.71%–104.45%) and RSD (3.77–5.81%) were obtained by adding S2− to rabbit serum and beverage (Table 4
                        ). Consequently, the synchronized fluorescence sensor proposed in this study can meet quantitative analysis requirements.
